 of Spohn's strategy for the\nderivation of the NLS \\cite{Spohn}, except for the final step of uniqueness.\nAdditional arguments are necessary to show that the objects constructed in\n\\cite{EESY} satisfy the assumptions of the unconditional uniqueness theorem.\nOnce we achieve this, we are able to prove the derivation result. In\nparticular, we show \\emph{Propagation of Chaos} for the defocusing\nGross-Pitaevskii hierarchy on $\\mathbb{T}^3$ for suitably chosen initial data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 May 2014 00:02:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-04-26"}
